<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-09-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="466" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to
                                    <persName type="to">Baron de Fava</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-09-14"><hi rend="italic">September 14,
                                    1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Answering your note of to-day, I
                            beg to say that the sense of the governor’s telegram was almost
                            textually given in my note to you, and that it is silent as to the
                            details you mention.</p>
                        <p>Hastily, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>